The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Friday, July 25, 2003 				 Penguin chief 
																								New Delhi July 24: Penguin India will soon have a new boss. Thomas Abraham is replacing David Davidar as president of the publishing house, reports our correspondent.																								David Davidar, CEO and publisher of Penguin India, is being transferred as publisher of Penguin Canada from January 1 next year. 																								Davidar, one of the founding members of Penguin India in 1985, will, however, continue his links with Penguin India as a director. 																								Davidars role as publisher at Penguin India is being farmed out to two new executive directors  Ravi Singh and V.K. Karthika.
